"{\"value\":{\"mdx\":\"# Installation\\n\\n## Prerequisites\\n\\n### Rust Toolchain\\n\\nThe ZCAM SDK packages include Rust bindings built via UniFFI. You need Rust installed with iOS targets:\\n\\n```bash\\n# Install Rust (if not already installed)\\ncurl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh\\n\\n# Add iOS targets\\nrustup target add aarch64-apple-ios aarch64-apple-ios-sim\\n```\\n\\n### Xcode\\n\\nXcode is required for iOS development. Install it from the Mac App Store.\\n\\n### Development Environment\\n\\n- Node.js 18+\\n- React Native 0.81+\\n- Expo SDK 54+ (if using Expo)\\n\\n## Installing Packages\\n\\nThe ZCAM SDK is divided into standalone packages. Install only what you need:\\n\\n```bash\\n# Full flow (capture, prove, verify)\\nnpm i react-native-zcam1-capture react-native-zcam1-prove react-native-zcam1-verify\\n\\n# Install native dependencies\\ncd ios && pod install\\n```\\n\\nIndividual packages:\\n\\n| Package | Purpose |\\n|---------|---------|\\n| `react-native-zcam1-capture` | Take photos with C2PA manifests |\\n| `react-native-zcam1-prove` | Generate ZK proofs for photos |\\n| `react-native-zcam1-verify` | Verify photo authenticity |\\n| `react-native-zcam1-picker` | Image picker with authenticity badges |\\n\\n:::warning\\nThe UniFFI bindings are built during `npm install`. This can take several minutes on first install.\\n:::\\n\\n## iOS Configuration\\n\\n### Bundle Identifier\\n\\nConfigure your app's bundle identifier in your project. For Expo apps, set it in `app.json`:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"expo\\\": {\\n    \\\"ios\\\": {\\n      \\\"bundleIdentifier\\\": \\\"com.yourcompany.yourapp\\\"\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### App ID for App Attest\\n\\nYou'll need your Apple Team ID combined with your bundle identifier. The format is:\\n\\n```\\n<TEAM_ID>.<BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER>\\n```\\n\\nFor example: `NLS5R4YCGX.com.yourcompany.yourapp`\\n\\nTo find your Team ID:\\n1. Open Keychain Access on your Mac\\n2. Find a certificate named \\\"Apple Development\\\"\\n3. The Team ID is the \\\"Organizational Unit\\\" field\\n\\n### Required Permissions\\n\\nAdd these keys to your `Info.plist` (or `app.json` for Expo):\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"expo\\\": {\\n    \\\"ios\\\": {\\n      \\\"infoPlist\\\": {\\n        \\\"NSCameraUsageDescription\\\": \\\"This app uses your camera to capture photos.\\\",\\n        \\\"NSPhotoLibraryUsageDescription\\\": \\\"This app needs access to save photos.\\\"\\n      }\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Environment Variables\\n\\nCreate a `.env` file with your configuration:\\n\\n```bash\\nEXPO_PUBLIC_APP_ID=<TEAM_ID>.<BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER>\\nEXPO_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL=https://your-backend-url.com\\n```\\n\\n## Running on Device\\n\\nApp Attest requires a physical iOS device—it does not work in the simulator (the SDK falls back to mock mode for development).\\n\\n```bash\\n# Expo\\nnpx expo prebuild\\nnpx expo run:ios --device\\n\\n# React Native CLI\\nnpx react-native run-ios --device\\n```\\n\\nOn first run, you may need to trust the developer certificate on your device:\\n**Settings → General → Device Management → Trust**\\n\",\"document\":[{\"href\":\"/getting-started/installation#installation\",\"html\":\"</header>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/getting-started/installation.mdx#installation\",\"isPage\":true,\"text\":\"\\n\",\"title\":\"Installation\",\"titles\":[]},{\"href\":\"/getting-started/installation#prerequisites\",\"html\":\"\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/getting-started/installation.mdx#prerequisites\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\n\",\"title\":\"Prerequisites\",\"titles\":[\"Installation\"]},{\"href\":\"/getting-started/installation#rust-toolchain\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>The ZCAM SDK packages include Rust bindings built via UniFFI. You need Rust installed with iOS targets:</p>\\n<pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\"># Install Rust (if not already installed)</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">curl</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> --proto</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> &#x27;=https&#x27;</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> --tlsv1.2</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> -sSf</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> https://sh.rustup.rs</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\"> |</span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\"> sh</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\" data-empty-line=\\\"true\\\"> </span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\"># Add iOS targets</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">rustup</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> target</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> add</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> aarch64-apple-ios</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> aarch64-apple-ios-sim</span></span></code></pre>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/getting-started/installation.mdx#rust-toolchain\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nThe ZCAM SDK packages include Rust bindings built via UniFFI. You need Rust installed with iOS targets:\\n# Install Rust (if not already installed)\\ncurl --proto &#x27;=https&#x27; --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh\\n \\n# Add iOS targets\\nrustup target add aarch64-apple-ios aarch64-apple-ios-sim\\n\",\"title\":\"Rust Toolchain\",\"titles\":[\"Installation\",\"Prerequisites\"]},{\"href\":\"/getting-started/installation#xcode\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Xcode is required for iOS development. Install it from the Mac App Store.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/getting-started/installation.mdx#xcode\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nXcode is required for iOS development. Install it from the Mac App Store.\\n\",\"title\":\"Xcode\",\"titles\":[\"Installation\",\"Prerequisites\"]},{\"href\":\"/getting-started/installation#development-environment\",\"html\":\"\\n<ul>\\n<li>Node.js 18+</li>\\n<li>React Native 0.81+</li>\\n<li>Expo SDK 54+ (if using Expo)</li>\\n</ul>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/getting-started/installation.mdx#development-environment\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\n\\nNode.js 18+\\nReact Native 0.81+\\nExpo SDK 54+ (if using Expo)\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"Development Environment\",\"titles\":[\"Installation\",\"Prerequisites\"]},{\"href\":\"/getting-started/installation#installing-packages\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>The ZCAM SDK is divided into standalone packages. Install only what you need:</p>\\n<pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\"># Full flow (capture, prove, verify)</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">npm</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> i</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> react-native-zcam1-capture</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> react-native-zcam1-prove</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> react-native-zcam1-verify</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\" data-empty-line=\\\"true\\\"> </span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\"># Install native dependencies</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\">cd</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> ios</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\"> &amp;&amp; </span><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">pod</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> install</span></span></code></pre>\\n<p>Individual packages:</p>\\n<table><thead><tr><th>Package</th><th>Purpose</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>react-native-zcam1-capture</code></td><td>Take photos with C2PA manifests</td></tr><tr><td><code>react-native-zcam1-prove</code></td><td>Generate ZK proofs for photos</td></tr><tr><td><code>react-native-zcam1-verify</code></td><td>Verify photo authenticity</td></tr><tr><td><code>react-native-zcam1-picker</code></td><td>Image picker with authenticity badges</td></tr></tbody></table>\\n<aside data-callout=\\\"warning\\\"><p>The UniFFI bindings are built during <code>npm install</code>. This can take several minutes on first install.</p></aside>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/getting-started/installation.mdx#installing-packages\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nThe ZCAM SDK is divided into standalone packages. Install only what you need:\\n# Full flow (capture, prove, verify)\\nnpm i react-native-zcam1-capture react-native-zcam1-prove react-native-zcam1-verify\\n \\n# Install native dependencies\\ncd ios &amp;&amp; pod install\\nIndividual packages:\\nPackagePurposereact-native-zcam1-captureTake photos with C2PA manifestsreact-native-zcam1-proveGenerate ZK proofs for photosreact-native-zcam1-verifyVerify photo authenticityreact-native-zcam1-pickerImage picker with authenticity badges\\nThe UniFFI bindings are built during npm install. This can take several minutes on first install.\\n\",\"title\":\"Installing Packages\",\"titles\":[\"Installation\"]},{\"href\":\"/getting-started/installation#ios-configuration\",\"html\":\"\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/getting-started/installation.mdx#ios-configuration\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\n\",\"title\":\"iOS Configuration\",\"titles\":[\"Installation\"]},{\"href\":\"/getting-started/installation#bundle-identifier\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Configure your app&#x27;s bundle identifier in your project. For Expo apps, set it in <code>app.json</code>:</p>\\n<pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">{</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#8DDB8C\\\">  &quot;expo&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: {</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#8DDB8C\\\">    &quot;ios&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: {</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#8DDB8C\\\">      &quot;bundleIdentifier&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: </span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&quot;com.yourcompany.yourapp&quot;</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">    }</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">  }</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">}</span></span></code></pre>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/getting-started/installation.mdx#bundle-identifier\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nConfigure your app&#x27;s bundle identifier in your project. For Expo apps, set it in app.json:\\n{\\n  &quot;expo&quot;: {\\n    &quot;ios&quot;: {\\n      &quot;bundleIdentifier&quot;: &quot;com.yourcompany.yourapp&quot;\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n\",\"title\":\"Bundle Identifier\",\"titles\":[\"Installation\",\"iOS Configuration\"]},{\"href\":\"/getting-started/installation#app-id-for-app-attest\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>You&#x27;ll need your Apple Team ID combined with your bundle identifier. The format is:</p>\\n<pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">.</span></span></code></pre>\\n<p>For example: <code>NLS5R4YCGX.com.yourcompany.yourapp</code></p>\\n<p>To find your Team ID:</p>\\n<ol>\\n<li>Open Keychain Access on your Mac</li>\\n<li>Find a certificate named &quot;Apple Development&quot;</li>\\n<li>The Team ID is the &quot;Organizational Unit&quot; field</li>\\n</ol>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/getting-started/installation.mdx#app-id-for-app-attest\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nYou&#x27;ll need your Apple Team ID combined with your bundle identifier. The format is:\\n.\\nFor example: NLS5R4YCGX.com.yourcompany.yourapp\\nTo find your Team ID:\\n\\nOpen Keychain Access on your Mac\\nFind a certificate named &quot;Apple Development&quot;\\nThe Team ID is the &quot;Organizational Unit&quot; field\\n\\n\",\"title\":\"App ID for App Attest\",\"titles\":[\"Installation\",\"iOS Configuration\"]},{\"href\":\"/getting-started/installation#required-permissions\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Add these keys to your <code>Info.plist</code> (or <code>app.json</code> for Expo):</p>\\n<pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">{</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#8DDB8C\\\">  &quot;expo&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: {</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#8DDB8C\\\">    &quot;ios&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: {</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#8DDB8C\\\">      &quot;infoPlist&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: {</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#8DDB8C\\\">        &quot;NSCameraUsageDescription&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: </span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&quot;This app uses your camera to capture photos.&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">,</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#8DDB8C\\\">        &quot;NSPhotoLibraryUsageDescription&quot;</span><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">: </span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">&quot;This app needs access to save photos.&quot;</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">      }</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">    }</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">  }</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">}</span></span></code></pre>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/getting-started/installation.mdx#required-permissions\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nAdd these keys to your Info.plist (or app.json for Expo):\\n{\\n  &quot;expo&quot;: {\\n    &quot;ios&quot;: {\\n      &quot;infoPlist&quot;: {\\n        &quot;NSCameraUsageDescription&quot;: &quot;This app uses your camera to capture photos.&quot;,\\n        &quot;NSPhotoLibraryUsageDescription&quot;: &quot;This app needs access to save photos.&quot;\\n      }\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n\",\"title\":\"Required Permissions\",\"titles\":[\"Installation\",\"iOS Configuration\"]},{\"href\":\"/getting-started/installation#environment-variables\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Create a <code>.env</code> file with your configuration:</p>\\n<pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">EXPO_PUBLIC_APP_ID</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">.</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\\\">EXPO_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL</span><span style=\\\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\\\">=</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\">https://your-backend-url.com</span></span></code></pre>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/getting-started/installation.mdx#environment-variables\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nCreate a .env file with your configuration:\\nEXPO_PUBLIC_APP_ID=.\\nEXPO_PUBLIC_BACKEND_URL=https://your-backend-url.com\\n\",\"title\":\"Environment Variables\",\"titles\":[\"Installation\"]},{\"href\":\"/getting-started/installation#running-on-device\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>App Attest requires a physical iOS device—it does not work in the simulator (the SDK falls back to mock mode for development).</p>\\n<pre class=\\\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\\\" style=\\\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\\\" tabindex=\\\"0\\\"><code><span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\"># Expo</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">npx</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> expo</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> prebuild</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">npx</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> expo</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> run:ios</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> --device</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\" data-empty-line=\\\"true\\\"> </span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\\\"># React Native CLI</span></span>\\n<span class=\\\"line\\\"><span style=\\\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\\\">npx</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> react-native</span><span style=\\\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\\\"> run-ios</span><span style=\\\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\\\"> --device</span></span></code></pre>\\n<p>On first run, you may need to trust the developer certificate on your device:\\n<strong>Settings → General → Device Management → Trust</strong></p>\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/getting-started/installation.mdx#running-on-device\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nApp Attest requires a physical iOS device—it does not work in the simulator (the SDK falls back to mock mode for development).\\n# Expo\\nnpx expo prebuild\\nnpx expo run:ios --device\\n \\n# React Native CLI\\nnpx react-native run-ios --device\\nOn first run, you may need to trust the developer certificate on your device:\\nSettings → General → Device Management → Trust\",\"title\":\"Running on Device\",\"titles\":[\"Installation\"]}]}}"
